excerpt: Bustling cantilever road bridge opened since 1943 and spanning the Hooghly River.
detail_description: The Howrah Bridge, also known as Rabindra Setu, is a bustling cantilever road bridge that spans the Hooghly River, connecting Kolkata and Howrah in Bengal. Built by the British and opened in 1943, it is one of the busiest bridges in India. Despite its age, it is referred to as the 'New Howrah Bridge' and stands as an enduring symbol of Kolkata.
name: Howrah Bridge
address: Kolkata, West Bengal 700001, India

detail_description: Belur Math, located downstream from Dakshineswar Kali Temple, spans 40 acres and serves as the central hub for the Ramakrishna Math and Mission. Established by Swami Vivekananda, a prominent disciple of Ramakrishna Paramahamsa, this serene site features a main shrine honoring Sri Ramakrishna with an architectural blend of Hindu, Buddhist, Christian, and Islamic influences.
name: Belur Math
address: Howrah, West Bengal 711202, India

excerpt: Elegant, domed, white marble museum, opened in 1921, housing displays on the history of Kolkata.
detail_description: Victoria Memorial is an exquisite white marble museum in Kolkata, built in 1921 as a tribute to Queen Victoria. The grand architecture and well-maintained gardens make it a popular spot for locals and tourists alike. Inside, the museum showcases the history of Kolkata and the British Empire in India. It also boasts a remarkable collection of over 5,000 paintings by renowned artists from the Bengal School of Art.
name: Victoria Memorial
address: Victoria Memorial Hall, 1, Queens Way, Maidan, Kolkata, West Bengal 700071, India

excerpt: Indian heritage museum with sections on archaeology, art, anthropology and geology, founded in 1814.
detail_description: The Indian Museum, founded in 1814, is a significant heritage site in India. It's the country's largest and oldest museum, featuring a diverse range of exhibits across its 35 galleries. Visitors can explore artifacts from various disciplines including archaeology, art, anthropology, geology, zoology and economic botany.
name: Indian Museum
address: 27, Jawaharlal Nehru Rd, Fire Brigade Head Quarter, New Market Area, Dharmatala, Taltala, Kolkata, West Bengal 700016, India

excerpt: 9 ornate spires top this riverside red and cream 1800s temple, with shrines to Krishna and Vishnu.
detail_description: Dakshineswar Kali Temple is a 1800s temple located on the eastern bank of the Hooghly River in Kolkata. It was built by Rani Rashmoni and features nine ornate spires in classic Nava-Ratna style. The temple is dedicated to Bhavatarini, a manifestation of goddess Kali, and also houses shrines to Krishna and Vishnu.
name: Dakshineswar Kali Temple
address: Dakshineswar, Kolkata, West Bengal 700076, India

excerpt: 269-acre botanic garden founded in 1786 with a serpentine lake, rare tree breeds & indigenous flora.
detail_description: Acharya Jagadish Chandra Bose Indian Botanic Garden, established in 1786, spans 269 acres and is home to over 12,000 plant species. The garden played a significant role in cultivating tea bushes smuggled from China by the British. It features a cactus house, palm collection, river overlook, and a boating lake with Giant Water Lily pads.
name: Acharya Jagadish Chandra Bose Indian Botanic Garden
address: Shibpur, Howrah, West Bengal 711103, India

detail_description: Vidyasagar Setu, also known as the Second Hooghly Bridge, is a magnificent cable-stayed bridge that spans the Hooghly River, linking Kolkata and Howrah. Named after the renowned Bengali reformer Ishwar Chandra Vidyasagar, it holds cultural and historical significance. Opened in 1992, it is the longest bridge of its kind in India and Asia.
name: Vidyasagar Setu
address: National Highway, 12, Kolkata, West Bengal 700022, India

excerpt: Prominent city thoroughfare featuring historic sites, boutiques, cafes & a vibrant nightlife.
detail_description: Park Street, also known as Mother Teresa Sarani, is a prominent thoroughfare in Kolkata, West Bengal. It is renowned for its historic sites, upscale boutiques, charming cafes, and vibrant nightlife. The street offers a wide array of internationally-recognized fast-food outlets, English-style pubs, hip nightclubs, and restaurants serving diverse cuisines. Additionally, it boasts western-style supermarkets and enticing bookshops.
name: Park St
address: Kolkata, West Bengal, India

excerpt: Monumental marble Hindu temple built between 1970 & 1996, with Krishna, Radha, Shiva & Durga idols.

Sponsored by the Birla family, it consists of three intricately carved temples dedicated to Lord Krishna and Goddess Radha in the main shrine, while the other two domes honor Lord Shiva and Goddess Durga. The entire structure is made of marble with towering pagoda-like monoliths at the entrance.
name: Birla Mandir
address: 29, Ashutosh Chowdary Ave, Ballygunge, Kolkata, West Bengal 700019, India

excerpt: Kolkata (formerly Calcutta) is the capital of India's West Bengal state. Founded as an East India Company trading post, it was India's capital under the British Raj from 1773–1911. Today it’s known for its grand colonial architecture, art galleries and cultural festivals. It’s also home to Mother House, headquarters of the Missionaries of Charity, founded by Mother Teresa, whose tomb is on site.
detail_description: Kolkata, formerly known as Calcutta, is the capital of India's West Bengal state and was once the capital of British India. The city boasts grand colonial architecture, vibrant art galleries, and a rich cultural heritage. It is also home to Mother House, the headquarters of the Missionaries of Charity founded by Mother Teresa. Kolkata's alleyways are now filled with cafes offering diverse menus and unique decor.
name: Kolkata
address: West Bengal, India

excerpt: Stately, 19th-century private residence with unique art & landscaped grounds, plus guided tours.

detail_description: Eden Gardens is a renowned 66,000-capacity cricket ground in Kolkata, India. It hosts various matches including Indian Premier League and international games. Despite its initial chaos, Kolkata promises an unforgettable experience for adventurous travelers.

address: Maidan, B.B.D. Bagh, Kolkata, West Bengal 700021, India

It is home to the final resting places of notable figures such as Walter Landor Dickens, Captain Edward Cooke, and Maj General Charles Stuart. detail_description: St. Paul's Cathedral is a significant Anglican church in Kolkata, completed in 1847. It boasts a restored steeple and remarkable stained glass windows. The cathedral stands as an impressive example of colonial architecture alongside the old Writers Building and the Victoria Memorial. Built to accommodate the growing European community, it resembles England's Norwich Cathedral with its pointed arches, buttresses, and vertical piers. St. Paul's Cathedral replaced St.

excerpt: Howrah is a city in the Indian state of West Bengal. Howrah is located on the western bank of the Hooghly River, opposite to its twin city of Kolkata. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Howrah, situated in the West Bengal state of India, is a bustling city on the western bank of the Hooghly River, facing its twin city Kolkata. It serves as the headquarters of the Howrah Sadar subdivision within Howrah district. One of its most iconic landmarks is the Howrah Bridge, a 450-meter-long structure without any pylon in the river.

address: West Bengal, India

detail_description: Santragachi Jheel, located in Santragachi, Howrah, is a popular destination for birdwatching and nature enthusiasts. The lake attracts migratory birds during the winter months, making it a picturesque spot for observing various bird species. Connected to Kolkata by two Hooghly River bridges, the jheel is easily accessible from all parts of the city. Additionally, visitors can enjoy views of the mesmerizing architecture of Howrah Bridge while exploring this scenic area.
name: Santragachi Jheel
address: Howrah, West Bengal

detail_description: Maidan is a sprawling green space in the heart of Kolkata, offering trails, picnic spots by the riverside, and various sporting venues including the famous Eden Gardens cricket ground. The area also features Victoria Memorial, a museum showcasing Indian and Western art, as well as St. Paul’s Cathedral. Families can enjoy attractions like Nehru Children’s Museum and M.P. Birla Planetarium nearby.
name: Maidan
address: New Market Area, Kolkata, West Bengal, India

excerpt: Traditional, domed planetarium & observatory featuring astronomy shows in multiple languages.
detail_description: M.P. Birla Planetarium, also known as taramandal, is a renowned domed planetarium and observatory located in Kolkata, India. This impressive white marble building is the largest of its kind in Southeast Asia and the second largest globally. Established in September 1962, it stands as a marvel of Indian architecture alongside iconic structures like the Sanchi Pagoda.
name: M.P. Birla Planetarium
address: Paul's Cathedral, 96, Jawaharlal Nehru Road, Cathedral Rd, Adjacent To St, Kolkata, West Bengal 700071, India

excerpt: Ornate mosque built in 1926, the largest in Kolkata with space for around 10,000 worshippers.
detail_description: Nakhoda Masjid, the largest mosque in Kolkata, is a stunning architectural marvel that showcases a blend of Islamic and Mughal styles. Completed in 1926, it features intricate details, including three domes and two 151-foot minarets. Modeled after Emperor Akbar's mausoleum in Agra, the mosque offers a serene atmosphere for prayer and reflection within its vast courtyard.
name: Nakhoda Masjid
address: 92, Rabindra Sarani, near Nakhuda masjid, Kolutolla, Kolkata, West Bengal 700073, India

detail_description: The Rail Museum, Howrah, is a top tourist spot in the area and houses a collection of historic railway artifacts including India's first electric locomotive and antique steam engines. Visitors can explore models, replicas, and exhibits showcasing the evolution of electrification. The museum features a miniature replica of Howrah railway station and offers a toy train ride for an immersive experience. While the premises are well-maintained, some visitors have expressed concerns about security personnel not being vigilant enough with the exhibits.

address: H8HQ+5XX, Rail Museum Toy Train Line, Howrah Railway Station, Howrah, West Bengal 711101, India

excerpt: Mother Teresa's tomb, preserved room & a small exhibit are on display at this quiet convent.
detail_description: The Mother House of the Missionaries of Charity in Kolkata is a serene convent that attracts visitors from around the world. It is a place where people can learn about the life and ideologies of Mother Teresa, a Nobel Peace Prize laureate and humanitarian. The house features her preserved room, tomb, and a small museum displaying items such as her sandals, drape, and eating bowl. Visitors can experience the peacefulness of her followers' beliefs and pay homage to her selfless sacrifice.
name: The Mother Teresa House Of The Missionaries Of Charity
address: 54A, Acharya Jagdish Chandra Bose Rd, near Ripon Street, opposite Bamboo Villa, Taltala, Kolkata, West Bengal 700016, India

excerpt: Ancestral home of the historic Tagore family, now a museum spotlighting its members’ lives.

The house, which is now part of Rabindra Bharati University, has been meticulously restored and serves as a tribute to Rabindranath Tagore, the creator of India's national anthem and a Nobel laureate.
name: Jorasanko Thakurbari
address: Ganesh Talkies, 267, Rabindra Sarani, Raja Katra, Singhi Bagan, Jorasanko, Kolkata, West Bengal 700007, India

excerpt: Museum housed in a historic building with exhibits & demonstrations devoted to science & technology.

Established in 1959, it is a prime attraction for science enthusiasts and students. The museum aims to promote an interest in science and technology among visitors, especially students. Housed in a historic building, it offers exhibits and demonstrations showcasing various aspects of science and technology.
name: Birla Industrial & Technological Museum
address: PHYSICS BLOCK, BIRLA INDUSTRIAL & TECHNOLOGICAL MUSEUM, 19A, Gurusaday Road Near Ballygunge Ice Skating Rink, 19a, Gurusaday Dutta Rd, Beck Bagan, Ballygunge, Kolkata, West Bengal 700019, India

excerpt: Temples, shrines & a museum dedicated to spiritual guru Sri Ramakrishna spread over a vast site.

excerpt: Scenic shoreline park with balustrades overlooking the water, landscaped gardens & amusement rides.

Situated beside the Ganges, it provides a peaceful and private ambiance with cool breezes perfect for romance.
name: Millennium Park
address: 12, Strand Rd, Bara Bazar, B.B.D. Bagh, Kolkata, West Bengal 700001, India

excerpt: Established in the 1870s, India's oldest zoo is a popular attraction & has 100+ species of animals.
detail_description: Located in Kolkata, the Zoological Garden, Alipore is India's oldest zoo, established in the 1870s. Spanning 46.5 acres, it houses over 100 species of animals and is a popular attraction for couples, families with kids, and wildlife enthusiasts. The zoo once housed Adwaita, the famous Aldabra giant tortoise believed to be over 250 years old at the time of its death.
name: Zoological Garden Alipore
address: 2, Alipore Rd, Alipur Zoological Garden, Alipore, Kolkata, West Bengal 700027, India

detail_description: Avani Riverside Mall is a vibrant and energetic shopping destination located across the 2nd Hooghly Bridge, catering to residents on both sides of the river. The mall offers a wide variety of branded shops, restaurants, and an attractive play area. Its riverside view adds a romantic touch to the overall experience. With grocery stores like Big Bazaar, gift shops like Archies, and trendy clothing at Pantaloons, there's something for everyone.
name: Avani Riverside Mall
address: 32, Jagat Banerjee Ghat Rd, Choura Bustee, Shibpur, Howrah, West Bengal 711102, India

detail_description: Mullick Ghat Flower Market, also known as the biggest flower market in Asia, offers a vibrant and chaotic atmosphere that is perfect for pre-wedding photography. With piles of colorful flowers like carnations, sunflowers, and marigolds creating a picturesque backdrop, it's a popular spot for capturing romantic shots. This more than 130-year-old market is the largest wholesale flower market in East India, attracting thousands of sellers daily.

address: p222, 1, Strand Bank Rd, Fairley Place, B.B.D. Bagh, Kolkata, West Bengal 700001, India

The center features interactive exhibits and cutting-edge technology to bring science to life, including 3D shows, motion simulation time machine, digital panorama, and robotic dinosaurs. Visitors can explore a maritime center, butterfly nursery, aquarium, outdoor maze, and toy train.

detail_description: Garden, also known as the Acharya Jagadish Chandra Bose Botanical Garden, is a historic 18th-century garden located just outside Kolkata. The garden also boasts half a million dried plant specimens from around the world and rare trees.
name: Garden

excerpt: Serene parkland features an artificial lake & over 70-acres of green space with shade trees & paths.

Spanning over 70 acres of lush green space with shade trees and pathways, it offers a serene atmosphere for visitors to enjoy nature. The lake was created in 1921 by excavating a marsh and has since become a popular destination for morning walkers and joggers.

detail_description: Eden Garden in Kolkata is a must-visit for cricket enthusiasts. It's renowned as one of the largest and oldest cricket grounds globally, with a seating capacity of 66,000. Home to the Kolkata Knight Riders team, it offers an amazing atmosphere filled with cheer and enthusiasm during matches. This iconic stadium has hosted numerous important cricket matches and is a favorite among fans. If you're passionate about cricket, visiting Eden Garden will be an unforgettable experience during your time in Kolkata.

It was funded through a public lottery and became the first Parish Church of Bengal. In 1815, it was designated as the primary Cathedral of Kolkata until St. Paul's Cathedral was consecrated in 1874.

This Greco-Roman landmark has a scandalous history, including its construction and subsequent usage by Governor-General Marquess Wellesley. Situated at the northern end of Dalhousie Square, it was initially used to house junior writers of the East India Company, hence its name.
name: Writers' Building

excerpt: Artifacts, photos & replicas of early public transportation displayed in a 1930s trolley car.
detail_description: The Smaranika Tram Museum in Kolkata is a unique museum housed in a refurbished 1930s trolley car, showcasing artifacts, photos, and replicas of early public transportation. As one of the few cities where trams still operate, Kolkata's long association with trams makes this museum a fitting tribute to its heritage. The museum's archives cover the history of various tram types, from horse-drawn trams to modern versions.
name: Smaranika Tram Museum

excerpt: Green space featuring a jogging/walking path, a pond & benches frequented by couples.

Spanning nearly 90,000 square feet, the park offers walkways, jogging tracks, restaurants, museums and outlets for visitors to enjoy.

detail_description: Sabarna Sangrahashala, established in 2005 by the Sabarna Roy Choudhury Paribar Parishad, is a museum located in the Barisha area of Kolkata.
